RESEARCH is a dataset-backed research CLI. You use it to:
- Get datasets in, inspect their schema, run analyses, and save results and artifacts (tables, charts, docs).
- Drive work with hypotheses, producing clear outputs you can revisit.

Start here:
1) Sign in
- research login

2) See what you already have
- research datasets ls            # remote datasets you can use
- research local ls               # local files RESEARCH can import

3) If you have a local file to use next
- research import "/absolute/path/to/file.csv" --name my_dataset --mode auto
Then:
- research describe my_dataset
- research query my_dataset "Show 10 example rows and basic field stats."

4) If you want to explore an existing dataset
- research describe <dataset_name>
- research query <dataset_name> "Top 20 records by <metric> with fields <a,b,c>."

5) If you have a hypothesis to test
- research plan <dataset_name> "Hypothesis: …"
- research run <dataset_name> --prompt "Test the hypothesis; subset=<…>; metrics=<…>; charts=<type, x, y>."

When you need data that isn’t in any dataset yet, create a research environment and pull in public sources and your files:
- research env create --dataset my_project --name "Baseline" --prompt "Acquire sources A,B; normalize to tables X,Y; validate Z; produce a dataset brief."
